FLOOR AND CEIL IN A SORTED ARRAY

You are given a sorted array of integers arr and a target integer k. Your task is to find two values:

Floor of k
The largest number in arr that is less than or equal to k

Ceil of k
The smallest number in arr that is greater than or equal to k

If either the floor or the ceil does not exist, return -1 for that value.

Your solution must run in O(log n) time complexity.

FUNCTION DESCRIPTION

Function name: findFloorCeil

This function finds the floor and ceiling of a given target value in a sorted array.

PARAMETERS

arr
A sorted array of strictly increasing integers

k
The target integer

RETURN VALUE

Return two integers:
floor and ceil

floor is the largest value in arr less than or equal to k
ceil is the smallest value in arr greater than or equal to k

Return -1 for floor or ceil if it does not exist

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ T ≤ 10
1 ≤ arr.length ≤ 100000
0 ≤ arr[i], k ≤ 100000
arr is sorted in strictly ascending order

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer T, the number of test cases

For each test case:
One line containing two integers n and k
One line containing n space-separated integers representing the array

OUTPUT FORMAT

For each test case, print two integers:
floor and ceil separated by a space

SAMPLE INPUT

3
6 6
1 3 5 7 9 11
5 10
2 4 6 8 10
4 3
5 10 15 20

SAMPLE OUTPUT

5 7
10 10
-1 5

EXPLANATION

In the first test case
Array is 1 3 5 7 9 11 and k is 6
Floor is 5 and ceil is 7

In the second test case
Array is 2 4 6 8 10 and k is 10
Floor is 10 and ceil is 10

In the third test case
Array is 5 10 15 20 and k is 3
Floor does not exist so it is -1
Ceil is 5

class Solution {
    public int[] findFloorCeil(int[] arr, int k) {
        int n=arr.length;
        int c=-1,f=-1;
        int left=0,right=n-1;
        while(left<=right)
        {
            int mid=(left+right)/2;
            if(arr[mid]==k)
            {
                f=arr[mid];
                c=arr[mid];
                return new int[]{f,c};
            }
            else if(arr[mid]<k)
            {
                f=arr[mid];
                left=mid+1;
            }
            else 
            {
                c=arr[mid];
                right=mid-1;
            }
        }
        return new int[]{f,c};
    }
}







class Solution {
    public int[] findFloorCeil(int[] arr, int k) {
        int n=arr.length;
        int l=0,r=n-1,f=-1,c=-1;
        while (l<=r){
            int mid=(l+r)/2;
            if(arr[mid]==k){
                f=arr[mid];
                c=arr[mid];
                return new int[]{f,c};
            }
            else if(k<arr[mid]){
                c=arr[mid];
                r=mid-1;
            }
            else{
                f=arr[mid];
                l=mid+1;
            }
        }
        return new int[]{f,c};
    }
}

